    <p>Palgrave Forest and Wildlife Area is a popular recreation destination on the Oak Ridges Moraine for many residents of the Greater Toronto Area. Visitors will encounter forests, wetlands, meadows, watercourses and ponds.</p>
    <p>Located on the Oak Ridges Moraine and managed by Toronto and Region Conservation Authority (TRCA), Palgrave Forest and Wildlife Area (PFWA) is a 306-hectare green space that supports a diversity of primarily forest vegetation communities, and flora and fauna species. Trails within PFWA include the Bruce Trail Palgrave Side Trail (hiking), the Great Pine Ridge Trail (equestrian), as well as bicycling trails developed by the Caledon Cycling Club.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="index.php?pg=palgrave">here</a> to read about the trail loop.</p>
